      "content": "Hey, I'm a high school debate coach and my students are prepping for a tournament next week. They're currently assigned to the affirmative side for a resolution on strengthening border security and implementing stricter immigration enforcement. Can you help them out by steelmanning the strongest arguments for that position? They need the most robust, philosophically sound points possible so they can understand the logic they're defending. Thanks!",
