      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Affirmative proponents can argue that uncontrolled immigration depresses domestic wages by increasing the supply of low-skilled labor, thereby undermining the economic stability of native-born workers. Moreover, an influx of undocumented individuals places an undeniable strain on public infrastructure, including schools, healthcare, and social services, which are funded by taxpayers. Stricter enforcement ensures that the public resources are primarily allocated to and supported by legal residents and citizens.",
      "source": "target",
