    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's helpful. My students are also worried about the \"humanitarian\" rebuttal they'll face. To be ready, they need to know how to counter the idea that strict enforcement is inherently inhumane. How would a debater frame the argument that strict enforcement actually supports a more humane and orderly system in the long run? I want them to have a very strong, principled defense for that side.",
